reviews.review_text:
Solid, Well-Played, Well-Recorded Show From start to finish this is a good show from Bird Song on.

Slight unidentifiable humm throughout (?).

warm up jam set 2 has a nice little warm up jam dissolving into Victim, I'm pretty sure that is the Munsters theme that Hornsby is playing with.  This was my first show that I actually got into.  I wish I were there for the first 2 shows.  oh well.  I love that grand piano...

Crazy Fingers...WOW I know everyone has their favorites, but this is the BEST Crazy Fingers I've ever heard.  The Big Man is locked in and it is a melodic masterpiece.  Of course it doesn't hurt that the version I am listening to is compliments of the FanTabulous Charlie Miller.  The powerful finish is just a nugget of goodness. 1991 is, IMHO the last "great" tour.

Soon You Will Not Hear His Voice.... Holy Shit !

*Where* has this show been hiding ?  (In plain sight as always, I'm sure....   :-)  )

The Crazy Fingers thru Terrapin sequence is the stuff of magic. Launch pad engaged - keep all arms and legs inside the ride vehicle at all times and take small children firmly by the hand... 

Happy treetops.

You won't be disappointed with this one.
My 1st birthday! great set, awesome crazy fingers and I cant believe they played all along the watchtower on my first birthday that is just sweet.

yep, that's a lovely Crazy Fingers very very nice.

good sound, very fine show esp for the era - really a lovely version of that special song tho (which was often done rather less well)
